Contractions are commonly used to make speech sound more natural and fluent. You're is a conrtaction of you are. This
constraction is a combination of the pronoun you and the verb are, which is part of the verb to be.

The verb to be is irregular. When conjugated with you, it becomes are. For example. You are an English learner.

Are can be used in the present affirmative to make a statement or ask a questions. This is a typical way to confirm someone's 
role or identity.

Transcript

